reviews: We really loved our stay here. We got a superior room. For Paris it was huge. Lovely hotel in a really great area. We could walk or cycle or get the metro so easily. Also great bars and restaurants nearby. Breakfast was excellent. Lovely staff too. Would highly recommend.it.

We stayed at this hotel for 2 days and it was amazing. we really enjoyed the charm and
welcoming attitude of the staff.
The GM I believe his name his Andreas, was super nice and always available to help.
We really look forward to going back again.

Nice little hotel, very good situated in Marais. The breakfast was great, especially that you could chose your own toast every morning. Two different restaurant, a lot of people on Saturday evening but we didn't hear anything and slept well in our room.
Would just loved if their where a pair of slippers...otherwise great!

We love staying in the Marais, and while this hotel is on a busy street, it’s a short walk to the more charming areas. The staff was very friendly and the room was spacious and had modern amenities. The breakfast was exceptional and we really enjoyed the fresh pastries, cheeses, meats and fruit. We loved the cool vibe and decor. Would stay here again!

We had a great stay at this unusual hotel. Well located, friendly staff, and rooms are spacious and well designed, that's rarely the case in Paris! enjoy the south American inspired decoration and the mexican restaurant next door is quite tasty as well

A beautifully decorated Hotel, our room was so special, modern, absolutely so clean and had everything you needed . huge TV and movies in all languages. Great bathroom and huge windows. such a comfortable bed and we slept so well. Breakfast has a choice of both cooked food and classic continental. The reception staff were so helpful. The cleaning staff were so professional. i would recommend this Hotel as one of the best i have been too for a long time.

I stayed one night at the hotel and found that the location is really good. There are many cute cafe close to it and it's convenient to go to the city center. My friend and I had a good time at 1K paris.

Staff was so welcoming and accommodating and helpful, it was my first time in Paris and I do not speak a word of French and they were very understanding. No complaints! Also have a wonderful taco restaurant next door and free coffee/espresso when you check in! What a delight!

The pillows inside the cases were disgusting (yellow and blood stained), if you're sensitive to noise it might not be the right hotel for you as the windows are not very sound proof.
Breakfast is very poor for a 4 star, and they wantes to charge me as the 650 euros i paid for 2 nights apparently didn't include breakfast.
Not a good value for money

Comfortable, great location! Spent to nights in 1K Paris. The neighborhood is very diversified. You can find all you need around: bars, groceries, clothes, etc. Did had the time to try the mescal bar, but, i’ll definitely come back. Totally recommend!

I visited Paris along with my girlfriend and we had an amazing experience staying at 1K Paris. The staff was friendly, helpful and accommodating. The design of the rooms and lobby were clean, welcoming and unique. We dined at the restaurant in the lobby and had amazing drinks and Peruvian food. We loved every minute of our experience here and will definitely be back!
-Michael P. and Elizabeth S.

My boyfriend and I visited 1K Paris for a few days and had a great visit! The woman at check in kindly greeted us with great care. Any request we had was swiftly accommodated without hesitation. The restaurants and bars on the premises offer such great Peruvian and Mexican food options. The ambiance was clean, warm and unique and we will definitely be back again next time in Paris!

The hotel absolutely exceeded our expectations. The staff was lovely and so helpful at every turn! The rooms are HUGE, which is always a welcome surprise. And the Taco stand downstairs serves wonderful drinks. We loved our stay and will be back!

I'm staying at the 1K Paris Hotel this week. Prior to booking I did a fair amount of research on what others have said about this property. Rarely am I totally pleased when I book a hotel. However, in this instance I have zero doubt I booked the best property for my needs.

Let me be specific about what went right.

1. Check-in experience. I was checked in by a cheerful, upbeat and most kind individual. Absolutely flawless check-in experience.
2. I got an inexpensive room. Despite this I have plenty of space. Lots of closet space, hangers, drawers and room for my toiletries in the bathroom.
3. Bed is very comfortable.
4. Bathroom is wonderful. Large heated towel rack, oversized bathrobe and big towels. Lovely bath amenities.
5. Quiet room.
6. Comfortable temperature.
7. Fridge with interesting mini-bar options.
8. Easy to use safe.
9. Cool lighting.
10. Amazing location. Access to Le Marais, Franprix market across street, Metro on the corner. Does not get much better.

I could get critical and make a few suggestions to improve this place. They could better position the shower head. Had to be careful I did not spray the floor at times. But I could easily deal with it as it is. A couple of minor lightbulbs were burnt out - no big deal.

Understand I am not paying 300 Euros a night. I'm paying less than 150 Euros each night with the deal I snagged through hotel2nite.com. For what I am paying it would be impossible to do better.

I will definitely be returning to this fun hotel.

Very nice hotel, very friendly staff.
The hotel is very close to transportation.
The room is bigger than all other hotels that we looked in Paris.
We will sure come back to this hotel next time we’ll visit paris.
Overall we really enjoyed our stay at 1k paris.
excludes the breakfast that wasn’t so rich.

Good, clean hotel with an excellent location. Plenty of nice restaurants, bars, cafes and shops around the area on Le Marais.

Very friendly receptionist staff who all spoke fluent (some native?) English.
Good and fast check-in/check out experience.

Room is simple but clean and quite big for Paris standards. Comfortable beds.

Hotel has a Peruvian restaurant (we didn't have a chance to try it) and a very cool Mezcal bar which we loved.

Overall we really enjoyed our stay. Only 'negative' thing I would mention would be that street noise can be heard a little. This didn't bother us at all, but if you're a light sleeper you might need to request a room not facing the street.

Lovely, small boutique hotel in an exceptional location in the Marais - the very best neighborhood to stay in Paris. Kind, attentive staff, comfortable beds and a reasonable amount of space make this hotel an excellent choice. The hotel also features a truly excellent Peruvian restaurant, a good Mexican restaurant next door - and many other great dining choices within a block or two. Within walking distance of many key attractions.

My sister and I stayed at 1K Paris for a girls trip to Paris. We thoroughly enjoyed our stay. Rooms were nice and clean- I loved how the windows opened and I could just relax and watch the folks walking below. It is in the perfect location- Le Marais is an awesome area of Paris with tons of shops and restaurants. Not a far walk to Notre Dame and the trendy St. Germain de Pres and Latin Quarter. There was also a subway station a half a block from the hotel. The staff was so friendly and helpful. They gave us perfect directions on how to get to Sacre Coeur using the subway, and then also printed them out for us so that we didn't get lost. They even left us a welcome package when we arrived- one of their mezcal drinks in a cute bottle on ice and 2 pastries. We would definitely come back again if we decide to visit Paris again.

The room was very stylish! It was spacious at 25 sq mts. The split bathrooms (one for washbasins, the other for bathing/loo) were spacious and premium. The people at the reception were friendly, always helping!

What an amazing stay at 1K hotel! The location was so great, metro was so near, loads of trendy cafes and it felt very safe. The staff were very friendly and accomodating. Rooms were very clean, lovely view from the window, bed comfy, huge bath tub and many amenities in the room. Would definitely stay here again at this hotel! Merci 1K team

I recently stayed at 1K Paris. Nothing was too much trouble from moving rooms as i don’t like perfume and first room though lovely smelt a lot of perfume from cleaning to organizing me a massage they were so good. the room was clean spacious and bright. check in and check out easy and you can communicate with reception via what’s app. v well located for marais and central paris and nice area easy to find taxis etc. i would definitely return. thank you

I always stay at the 1K Hotel when I visit Paris! And all the members are super friendly and make you feel at home away from home!
Everything is so clean, and they have good restaurants! I loved it even more after the pandemic. I will come back

Amazing stay! The location was great, in walking distance from a metro, loads of trendy bars and cafes around and it felt very safe. The staff were very accomodating and friendly, although we couldn’t check in early we could leave our bags with them and on our last day we did the same after check out. Rooms were very clean, lovely view from the window, bed comfy, huge bath tub and many amenities in the room. Would definitely stay here again!

Good placed hotel. Many sightsseing opportunities, very professional staff which looked after us. Issues where solved immediately. Just ask for a quiet room if you a sensible to road noise of the avenue. Reccomended restaurants and non touristic places.

Nice looking hotel, great location and friendly staff. However, that's kind of where the good stuff stops.

Unfortunately the room (on the 5th floor) was very warm and there was no Aircon etc. This was in spring so in summer I think it would be unbearable (and I've previously lived in SE Asia).

There are signs up to enjoy happy hour around the hotel bar but we were told it wasn't actually a bar so we were sent to the secret mescal bar where you choose drinks based on your BDSM preferences apparently (who knew toe sucking could be so tasty?).

Overall, it wasn't a bad place, it just wasn't great either.

My fiancée and I literally loved the hotel. The location is just perfect, few steps from the Marais (one of my fave area in Paris!). We had the chance to have a dinner at the restaurant of the hotel, the InKa, perfect Peruvian food. Definitely gonna recommend this place. Room was super clean.

The hotel was perfectly located and also the area around is full of life. The room was super clean and the stuff really friendly. I would definitely visited it again. The restaurant was exceptional and a new culinary experience. Totally recommend.

This hotel is in a great location.
Everyone was so helpful!
The girls at the front desk were all great!! Especially the one with the on point makeup and the other young female both of whom spoke Spanish. The night time guy was so helpful!!! Anything we needed help with he would come up to help( the television, the ac , a replacement sheet). Staff is amazing, those 3 need a raise!
The rooms are on the small size , the shower situation is super odd especially if you are with friends as the glass is see through .
I would recommend this hotel more for couples at least the smaller room.
Overall happy with my stay.

I stayed here for the first time and I have to say it’s my new favorite hotel of Paris. The rooms are creatively decorated and the beds are so comfy! There are two restaurants connected - Inka is super delicious and El Venico has amazing tacos! There’s even a ‘secret’ Mezcaleria with super fun drinks! Will definitely come back again!

I stayed 2 nights in 1K in Paris with one of my friend
We had a great time
The location of the hotel is perfect, close to everything by walk and quiet
The food was very nice
Bed are super confortable and we had bath in our room as well
We lived breakfast in bed
Absolutely recommend 1K if you need a place in Paris ! Will go again for sure

The hotel is very well situated, perfect for wandering the streets of the Marais and with lots of lovely places to eat nearby. There is easy public transport access from CDG and Orly airport. The staff are polite and helpful and the rooms are modern, bright and airy. I would highly recommend a stay here.

What a wonderful stay at 1K Paris! In a terrific location with an uber-friendly staff, spacious rooms, & delicious cocktails and bites. Thrilled they had availability for me while also honoring my pandemic cancellation with credit. Staff was wonderful, friendly, and welcomed me back! Highly recommend the 1K Paris on your next visit!

I came back after last summer cause I loved the place, and was not disappointed! Great location, friendly staff, comfortable room, nice breakfast, good coffee.
So I might come back every time I travel to Paris!

Perfect all around. Staff is customer service driven. Room is clean, spacious, modern and calm (courtyard side). Food is excellent. Walking distance to everything: Le Marais, Île de la Cité, etc. Will be back!

Amazing service - staff are kind, lovely and help you with everything you need.
The room is equipped, have a big size and very comfortable.
Location is great, in the heart of Paris.
I took a massage in the spa which was one of the best I had in my life.
Highly recommended

2 stars: one for the food, one for the decoration. The rest was really poor. No hot water, extremely slow service, blackout curtains broken or inefficient, noise in the room from 7.20am. Rooms vary a lot from one to the other so you might either get very lucky or very unlucky. No standard/middle ground. Ready to test your luck?

We enjoyed our stay at the 1K. Staff was very helpful--at front desk, in restaurant and bars, as well as cleaning and maintenance crew, who quickly replaced a broken coffee machine. The neighborhood is fun to walk around, with many charming bars and restaurants, and it's convenient to the Métro, to get to any sight in Paris that you care to visit. We would definitely return, and recommend to friends.

Very Nice hotel, nice room, clean, friendly staff, great location, good value for money!
It was important to me to write something but I have no more characters to fill the 200 that needed for publishing the review.

My daughter and I enjoyed our stay at this hotel. We loved the decor and our room was a great size. We enjoyed breakfast, found the staff very helpful and also loved the hidden cocktail bar. The location is brilliant also.
Our only problem was our room was to the front and without ear plugs on our first night we didn’t sleep a wink. We bought some the next day which helped a lot but for us it was incredibly noisy. Maybe this wouldn’t affect some people but we wouldn’t be used to any noise like this so I’d be asking for a room at the back or definitely bringing earplugs. Other than that it’s a super hotel.

This hotel is not only GORGEOUS with spacious rooms to die for, the staff are lovely, and helpful with meticulous attention to detail. Fabulous fitness room, stellar location - I can't say enough good things... I cannot wait to go back!

The hotel 1k is located in the marais district, one of the hippest districts of paris. The train station and the city center can be reached quickly and easily thanks to the nearby metro station and bus station (approx. 150m). The hotel impresses with absolutely quiet rooms on the inner courtyard side, fantastically comfortable beds and a very friendly staff who fulfill all wishes.
In summary a great stay in a recommendable hotel.

I had a great room! Cool view of courtyard and had a huge tub to soak in! Best guacamole in Paris! Super cool neighborhood (Le Marais) never a dull moment! The staff here are the best! Thank you! Fabulous shops and secret gardens all over the place.

Unnecessary Complicated Check-In, didn't accept credit cards. Payment was only possible with cash or online banking. Insufficiently working keycard. Pre arrival Online Check-In without any use.

Rooms are OK. Bar was closed.

Good location

My trip to Paris was made all the more enjoyable by my stay at the 1K Hotel in the Marais. The room was large, particularly for Paris standards. I'll definitely stay here again and will be recommending to my friends and family. This boutique hotel has their own taqueria and bar on the bottom floor, and I must say the tacos were amazing. Being from LA I know my tacos, so I wasn't really expecting much in Paris. But when I looked in the window and saw the chef making homemade tortillas, I was hopeful. There are other bars, bistros, a Tibetan Restaurant, bakeries, clothing stores, only 2 - 5 minutes walk in either direction. I really didn't have to leave the block to have a great Parisian experience. But since the Filles du Calvaire metro station is a 3 minute walk down the block, this hotel was the best staging ground for all of my escapades all over Paris. I was very thankful that the hotel staff was very attentive to my needs and always went above and beyond to recommend the best places for me to go around the city.

The hotel offers very spaceous, quiet and clean rooms, a cosy and personal atmosphere, beautiful decoration and excellent service. We surprisingly got an update on our room booking! Breakfast is diverse and offers everything you could wish for. The hotelis perfectly located in one of my favourite areas in Paris, surrounded by many restaurants and bars. I look forward and hope to be back very soon. I can definitely recommend this hotel to everyone for a wonderful stay in Paris.

Great location, perfect rooms , friendly staff.

Breakfast ok but not great. You have to choose 1 day ahead, cereal is only muesli bread only 1 slice baguette and no choice on portions. Some way to big other to small like croissant are mini size.

Great location, beautiful and clean rooms! Great service, amazing staff!!! Very much recommend, and will come back. The workers helped us a lot and gave great service. My husband and I had the greatest time in 1k hotel Paris. Comfortable rooms, 24 hour front desk, incredible!

Pleasantly surprised by the room size and features. Convenient to 5 and 8 Metro lines and walkable to Marais. Our room faced the quiet courtyard with no noise from the restaurant and bar even when they were going strong three floors below. The only weakness was a lack of English TV. Fully understand we are in Paris, but it's fair to expect more language variety.

Even though I live in Paris, I was looking for an one-night experience to escape a little, even inside the city. With all the security manners, I had the chance to find an excellent deal that the Hotel offered and I couldn't be more surprised. Excellent room, very illuminated, with a comfortable king-size bed and a bathtub that took away my stress. The television surprised me with a very large options of movies - I watched three! The dinner was a Mexican experience with delicious tacos, guacamole, drinks and a delicious cookie. For the breakfast, I woke up with a really pleasant French petit-déj, couldn't get any better. Merci.

I was pleasantly surprised by the tastes of the room. Despite being on boulevard du temple it is very peaceful. Besides being spotlessly clean, the staff is very helpful and friendly. Not to be missed, also because the area is quite lively

Excellent experience during my stay at 1K hotel as curfew hasn’t allowed any dine-out but 1K hotel got you covered with their best tacos and Mezcal cocktails menu, and nice little breakfast. Felt very welcomed by the staffs even one of them spoke with me in my own language (Malay)! Spacious room which is rarely found in Paris, not to mention their bathroom is pleasantly comfortable. Definitely will my choice for my next visit to Paris!

I have come back often for business trips at this hotel. The decoration is original, tacos served by the restaurant are delicious and bed is amazing. Very nice staff and clean place. I will keep coming back :)

Stayed here for 3 nights between 12 - 15 January 2021. Gabriela was the first person I met there and she was nice and sorted out my booking quite fast. I got room 414 on the fourth floor, the room has a double bed, private bathroom, TV, air con and mini bar. Everything was clean and in order.

The breakfast is delivered to your room during the pandemic and it's deliciously cooked. The staff is accommodating of your needs, I requested double portions one morning and they were more than happy to do so.

There is a gym in the basement with cardio machines and weights. I trained there twice and it is pleasant and quiet. There is a TV that you can use to start music. The gym is air conditioned.

The hotel is in Republique, the area is a busy central with many shops and restaurants. Metro station is like 3 mins walk.

One downside is I couldn't catch the reception 4 out of 5 times when calling from my room. I had to go downstairs to talk to them about my query. Nothing major though.

Overall, great hotel and would book here whenever I come to Paris. Highly recommend.

I needed a last minute hotel for 2 nights, this was a great choice! Super friendly staff, comfortable bed, nice hot shower, great lighting (you can change the color of light by your bed, love that :) Covid means the restaurants and bar are closed, but they look like they would be wonderful when open. Mini-bar with snacks in room, but no coffee / tea (which I didn't mind). Generally a great stay, I would come back for sure. Thanks!

Wonderful experience in great location. People are 5 stars. They made my stay special. Boutique hotel with large modern room between place de la Bastide and République. Metro super close. Maybe if it wouldn't have been covid time I woukd have given 5 stars.

I stayed for 7night for work when Paris was a red zone with alerts for Covid-19. Paris was bizarre and empty.
The staffs are very warm and available, ready to reply you with smile. It was a sort of a bubble with full of piece and this made me feel very relaxed and safe from all the things going around from the city.
The rooms has many lights and bright- bathroom is essential but clean. The best part of my staying was the beds. Linens are very crispy & well ironed and the mattress is just too comfortable. Amenities is In decent quality. I didn’t try breakfast / room service but I can tell that will be also well cared.
The only uncomfortable thing is the position of power socket. If you want to use phone while charging, a normal length cable could be little uncomfortable. But the rest is good.
Highly recommended, very good compromise between price-quality 👍

We actually live nearby but checked in to the hotel during a terrible heatwave this summer. The hotel Air Conditioning does the job and we had a comfortable stay. Good rates and helpful staff.

The hotel is in a very good location. Walking distance from countless restaurants, bars, coffee shops, and attractions.

NEVER send an email to all people that stayed in your hotel without hiding their emails by putting them in the BCC field. Such negligence with personal data is worrisome for a place that keeps a copy of your ID and credit card.

Nice, big rooms and very comfy bed. Lots of space for us and our toddler, who really enjoyed the bathtub, the huge tv. Great area close to nice restaurant and drinks. Helpfull personel at the entrance.

Amazing weekend at 1k hotel! I’ve stayed in a range of hotels in Paris and 1k has by far the biggest, most up to date, and comfortable rooms (including bathrooms!). The air conditioning kept our room cool when we emerged from walking around all day in the summer Parisian heat. The staff was accommodating, offering water bowls or our dog, and also spoke great English. The restaurant attached provided the perfect venue for happy hour drinks (highly recommend the mezcal slushies). Finally the location allowed us to meander down the streets of the Marais, then take the Metro right back to the hotel where a stop is located. Traveling during a pandemic can be stressful, but the professionalism of the staff put any worries at ease. Can’t wait for another weekend at 1k.

I stayed at the 1K several times since last year and never been disappointed - good value for money, centrally located , quiet rooms and nice staff ! and very import = large rooms which is quite rare in Paris !

Ok hotel, friendly staff. Everything is fine, but small stuff missing: lighting on dark carpet staircase, plug in sink, showerscreen, bed is not too comfy and general finishing is a little clumsy. Not so much walking distance from hotspots.

A great hotel to stay in. Clean, friendly, modern and well-located. Just a heads up, our room and en suite were open plan so no privacy if you’re sharing with friends (check ahead if this would bother you). Highly recommend this hotel!

Located in Le Marais, closely to restaurants, boutique shops, and night entertainment. Room size is big compared to typical Paris hotels. Excellent in-house Peruvian restaurant and great piscos. Very clean. Helpful staff. Located off a big street so if you are looking for a typical Parisian street view, this is not it. Would stay here again.

I stayed 3 nights in a superior room on the third floor. Room 335 was spacious with a large open bathroom. WiFi was poor, room was poorly cleaned with, amenities not replaced, coffee cups not cleaned. Despite COVID 19 the breakfast buffet was maintained. Poor limited choice. Greasy dirty tables at the restaurant. Some staff are friendly others just ignore customers. I never felt I was in a 4 stars hotel. Just an average expensive boutique hotel located in central paris. Very noisy bar on the ground floor.

Great boutique 4 star hotel in the nice (local) part of Le Marais. Rooms are modern and very clean. Staff is helpfull and pleasant. Nice restaurant which serves great food. Rooms are quiet and boost a modern atmosphere.
Highly recomended

The suite with the swimming pool really is as divine as seen on the pictures - the scene is truly unique in Paris with a view over the Paris roofs - it was a great opportunity to shoot there and to direct a video, and I was glad to discover this hotel - i hope to be back someday without a work assignement to really enjoy the pool and the scene there - and thank you Alexander for your wall welcome

Our visit to this hotel couldn't have been any better. As one of the very few hotels still working in Paris, our stay was very accomodating and the staff was more than helpful. The food in the restaurant was one of the best that I had on my trip; I highly recommend the ceviche.
We are planning to return in December, and we will be staying here again.

Very well located, this hotel is a real 4 stars with wonderful rooms and large bathrooms. Since my arrival till my departure, the staff was very helpful. The breakfast is rich, and the hotel have a very nice restaurant and a wonderful hidden club. Recommended, will go back there as soon as possible.

The rooms were lovely and clean, the service was friendly, and the restaurant adjacent to the hotel had great food, albeit slightly expensive. The room itself was very spacious and furnished well. I would definitely return!

Good Location and very good service. Great rooms.Breakfast also very good. Gym looked good but no time to use as only short stay.
Staff also very helpful and a free drink at the bar as first stay was a bonus.

I have stayed here on several occasions and it is one of my favourite hotels in Paris. The location is fantastic and easily accessible from the airport. The rooms are bright and airy and the staff are incredibly kind and helpful. I would highly recommend it.

We stayed at 1K for almost 7 days and our stay was wonderful. Location is perfect if you are interested in exploring a fun and young area of Paris. The rooms were spacious and comfortable. The staff was welcoming, kind, and attended to all of our needs.

Our room was incredibly spacious, especially compared to other Parisian hotels. We had a standard King room, which came with two sinks and a large closet space. We were instantly comfortable. The bed was comfy as well as the shower and bathroom amenities. The hotel provided complimentary water too, which was nice. The location was very central and easy to access two major metro stations.

This was my second stay at this hotel and I had liked the first time very much. Which is why I had booked again. Paris being Paris, hotels remain on the pricey side even after one year of social unrest and two months of strikes ;-) For over $1,000 for 4 nights, one can expect a decent breakfast and friendly staff. I had none of these. The room I was in was comfortable except for the shower head. The water pressure was a bit low and the tub was not convenient as should you want to draw a bath, you had to use the shower head to fill the tub. But other than that and paper maché walls, the room was nice. The reception staff is kinda friendly not over friendly but kinda. As for the breakfast staff, one of the girls (dark haired) needs to be trained as to how to deal with customers. The blonde lady was very nice and welcoming. I had to beg for ketchup every day, and every day they’d bring back a couple sachets they would leave by the eggs. Just a couple! So every day I had to ask. I stopped asking today and as there was none I will never know if they had finally run out... But the cherry on the cake was today. After waiting for 10 mn for them to refill the eggs, they brought the weirdest looking scrambled eggs I had ever seen in my entire life. I know scrambled eggs can be weird in non English speaking countries but I had had them the three first days and they were ok. Today, they were so yellow that they looked barely cooked (photo attached). When I made the attendant (dark haired one) aware of the situation she lifted the lid with a stiff upper lip and said, “no they’re ok.” I went to the reception to complain and the guy came over and said they looked ok but went to the kitchen to enquire. When you see the pic you will understand. Their chef is “Mexican American” so he knows how to make them! Well, I’m not Mexican but French American and I do know how to make them as well. The receptionist was much nicer than the dark haired girl working the buffet and offered to cook them more. At least he cared. I have lived abroad for the last 20 years and have been living in Bogotá, Colombia for the last 3 years traveling through Latin America on a weekly basis and some of the staff on this hotel lack the basics in hospitality.

I stayed at the 1K for a business trip.
The location is just great, very central and at 15minutes from Paris Nord.
Amazing food, the breakfast was the best!
Also we’ve been very surprised to find a speak easy bar on the back of the kitchen that served mezcal cocktails.
Definitely recommend!

Opted to stay here for a work trip and was pleased I picked this place.
Staff are nice and helpful on check-in, very helpful recommending restaurants, although they did say the Peruvian one on site is particularly good. I took their advice on this and really enjoyed the meal too.
Gym was ok, nothing special but has everything you’d need.
I’d stay again for sure

Hotel was in a great location. Near a Metro station, although workers were on strike and not working. Lots of galleries, restaurants and shops within a short walk.

Our room on 5th floor, on the back side, over looking a courtyard, room 511. It was well appointed, quite spacious. Bathroom and marvelous deep tub.

Would highly recommend staying here. The only glitch was check in. We arrived from a flight from San Francisco around 11:00 a.m. They told us to leave our bags and come back at 3:00. We arrived at 3:30, the room wasn't ready. Told us 5 more minutes. At 4:00 they said it's ready, only to go upstairs to find the maid just starting to clean the room. Could have been handled much better.

This is a well located hotel, with very spacious and modern rooms. All staff were most helpful staff throughout stay. We were also visiting at the time of the metro strikes and staff gave us the best tips for getting around. The hotel was also well located as we could walk to the majority of tourist sites. Definitely would stay here again and recommend it to anyone wanting to visit Paris - we stayed here for 4 nights..

We had a great stay, it was perfectly clean, warm and dry, which was very much appreciated in the cold weather! Very quiet also as double glazing and thick curtains completely blocked out the noise and light from the street below. Great location too and staff were really helpful. I’d definitely go back and recommend to family and friends.

We spent 2 nights here over Thanksgiving weekend. It seemed small at first glance, but the rooms were very nice size with good bathrooms. All three rooms we had were different but all were clean, comfortable & stylish. It was a little noisy as our rooms faced the main street. The breakfast buffet was fine, but nothing over the top. When our son was sick on our check out day, they let us stay in that room until 3 pm. Very kind of them.

We are young couple of artists and me, and my wife we found what we were looking for. We stayed in spacious rooftop room which is a two floor suite with balcony pool and Parisian rooftop view, and separate shower on the second floor, and comfortable king size bed, and separate bathtub on the first floor. Bathtub is best with wine that can also be found in the hotel room. Hotels wine choice is great. Rooftop view is the best at sunset, or sunrise. Amazing chill spot to sit, smoke, talk, drink and just enjoy. The pool can be a challenge in December, but Paris is really not that cold so, if you get lucky with having some sun and no wind you can feel quite good in the pool. Hot shower is on the same floor right next to the pool. Overall we were looking for great location, aesthetic, space, all inclusive relaxation and also place that tells a story through image and we got that.

Wonderful atmosphere, very large rooms, gym, cocktail bar, delicious restaurant, very nice people ... what else ?
The hotel Is located in a wonderful part of Paris, very close to subway and surrounded of a lot of interesting bar.
My favourite hotel in Paris !!!

We had an amazing staying during the last weekend of November.
The location of the hotel is great if you want to not be surrounded by hundreds of tourists but still live the city.
The staff made us feel like at home and the manager of the hotel had a unique detail.
Definitely, it will be in top of our minds if we return to Paris soon!

Thank you! we had a wonderful visit the room was very clean, the beds extremely comfortable, loved the bathrooms and decor! we took advantage of the breakfast and found it extremely enjoyable but the best part was the Mescaleria Bar! we will be back. Kim R

The hotel room was very nice and clean. The decor is amazing and I love the bar! The breakfast was delicious. The hidden treasure was the speakeasy in the back of the kitchen. I will definitely come back.

Great location, very friendly staff, cool interior design and large rooms. The hotel restaurant serves delicious food and the drinks at the Pisco bar was very good and also delicious drinks at the Mescaleria.
Only downside was that our room faced another place which must be a night club with a very loud audience which disrupted a good night sleep.

This is a really nice small hotel in a great location in Le Marais. The area is full of interesting shops, bars and restaurants, and the hotel is well placed for Metro. The front desk will call a cab for you to the hotel. The hotel staff are friendly and helpful and speak English.We arrived at 10.30 hoping to drop our bags, to find our rooms were available, which was great.

The room was lovely, stylish, comfortable, light and airy, and well equipped. There was a little noise from the bar below the window, but the glazing is very good, and it didn’t go on too late. I understand from friends that the rooms over the street are noisier, so check when you book if this is an issue. I foundit a veryquiet hotel for a city.

Breakfast was very good, great continental selection plus hot bacon, sauage and scrambled eggs.

We didn’t really use the bar or restaurant as we were out, but the bar was very popular with locals on the Saturday night, and has lots of different tequila cocktails!

All inall a really nice stay, I stayed here with friends but will return with my husband.

The staff at this hotel were super kind and friendly! The rooms were super clean and had a lot of room if you book the M Superior. The location of the hotel is fantastic, it is in a happening area with lots of bars, restaurants, and boutiques for shopping- yet it is quiet enough at night where you can have a good nights rest. The actual bar and restaurant at the hotel is superb, I high suggest visiting this hotel whether or not if you do or do not decide to not book it because the food and drinks are phenomenal!

Excellent hotel, with very friendly English speaking staff. Funky decor, nice to have something a bit different while staying in Paris, and the rooms + bathrooms are good sized. The hotel location is good, 10 min walk to the Place de la Bastille. Would also recommend the breakfast, and good continental selection, with a few hot/English breakfast options.

My fiance and I had a wonderful experience with 1k Paris. Staff was super nice and welcoming, the rooms and hotel were cleanly, and even though we were facing a major street it was a very quiet hotel which allowed for a good night rest. The location was excellent! Its near a bunch of boutique shops, restaurants, bars, and overall a lively area of Paris but respectfully quiet as well. It's not overwhelming like the areas of large tourist attractions in places near the Eiffel Tower or Campse- Elysse. The hotel has a wonderful restaurant and bar that becomes busy on the weekend. It is well worth it to make a reservation and check it out! The Peruvian food was one of a kind and delicious!!! We highly recommend this hotel to couples and friends. Overall, the hotel is gorgeous, very unique, comfortable, and friendly!

Nice hotel, modern and young staff. Good breakfast although the coffee was moderate. Tip: change the furniture in the restaurant. Really low and heavy chairs and tables that give no room for the legs.
Spacious room, nice light colours.

I stayed here with my 10 year old daughter for her birthday. We loved it! Amazing atmosphere and very nice decor. super friendly staff, very welcoming to both me and my daughter. great location: close to la place de la republique, we walked to the Louvre, Gallery Lafayette and in le marais, a lovely neighbourhood with nice little shops and restauranrs. The restaurant of the hotel is very good as well. The room was very clean,nice and even rather ‘big’ considering parisian standards. We highly recommand and will go back!

Thoroughly enjoyed my stay at the 1K Paris. The room was very comfortable, great size, quiet, with a great bathroom. Just a warning that there isn't a door between the bathroom and bedroom; not a problem for single travelers. Mini bar, coffee maker, fridge, very comfortable bed, plenty of storage/closet space, towel warmers, bathtub and shower, very pleasant and friendly staff at front desk and in housekeeping.Great value for the money in Central Paris. Metro access is just 200 feet from the hotel. I would definitely stay here again in the future.

The room was quiet, comfortable and roomy, the staff were friendly and helpful, and the bar and restaurant looked nice, though I didn’t partake. Great location for the main tourist attractions, but out of the fray a bit.

The hotel interior looks fascinating. Except for, the staff in the hotel were great, everyone was very polite and ready to help in any situation. The room was huge on two floors, and very clean! The hotel has also an excellent location and is located in a very safe zone of Paris! Had a great time there. If I decide to go again to Paris, I will definitely book this hotel again :)

Me and my friend were in this hotel for 5 days.
Hotel is really beautiful, decoration in reception and restaurant is amazing. Staff was really friendly and they wanted to help us all the time. Breakfast is also really good.
Rooms are SO amazing. We were in a room with 2 floors some kind of ''duplex room''. It was so lightly, big, with 2 bathrooms, confortable, very clean, 3 closets...
Location of the hotel is also really good. We had 2 metro stations, one 20 seconds walking, and other after 3 min walking.
The street where hotel is located is full of restaurants, stores, pharmacies...
So, you will have all you need.
I would love to say something about the pool, but because we traveled on October, we couldnt try it... but it looks really nice and I am sure that in summer must be amazing.
They also offer a 24h gym, which is amazing.
I had a really nice experience on this hotel and I know that if I come back to Paris soon, I will definatly come back to 1K paris.

I’m visiting Paris every 4 months a year. This is the best hotel I have visited for many years. Location is perfect, rooms are clean and bright . It’s a nice design hotel in the Marais. And the staff is very friendly:)

It was my second time in this gorgeous very stylish boutique hotel. You feel just at home as the staff is warm and helpful. The rooms are stylish and the location is ideal! Definitely recommend this place to stay while in Paris.

This hotel is perfect. Great location, less than one minute walk to train station, best breakfast in Paris, super friendly staff, good WiFi, rooms are very roomy and comfortable I wish I can give this hotel 10 stars.
